---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About This Site — Pinehurst Golf Trips"
  description="Why this site exists, who's behind it, and how the content is written. An independent Pinehurst golf trip planning resource built by a golfer, not a marketing team."
>
  <section class="pt-28 pb-20 md:pt-32 md:pb-28 px-6">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-dark-green">
        About This Site
      </h1>

      <div class="mt-10 prose">
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl text-dark-green font-bold">Why this exists</h2>
        <p>
          When I started planning my first trip to Pinehurst, I had a lot of questions. Which courses are worth the money? Do I need to stay at the resort? How do caddies work? What's the realistic cost?
        </p>
        <p>
          The answers were scattered across resort marketing pages, forum threads, and one-off blog posts. There was no single, independent resource that laid it all out honestly. So after my trip, I built one.
        </p>
        <p>
          I still see the same questions come up online all the time — people trying to piece together a plan from fragments. This site is my attempt to save them the legwork and help them have an incredible trip to the Pinehurst area.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl text-dark-green font-bold mt-16">Who I am</h2>
        <p>
          I've been playing golf for about 30 years. Before kids I played to about a 1 handicap; these days I'm more of a 5. I live about 3.5 hours from Pinehurst and took my first trip there in 2024.
        </p>
        <p>
          I'm not affiliated with Pinehurst Resort, any course, or any tourism board. Nobody is paying me to write this. The opinions are mine, and I'll tell you when something is based on research rather than firsthand experience.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl text-dark-green font-bold mt-16">What I've played</h2>
        <p>
          I have firsthand experience on these courses and write about them in first person:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Pinehurst No. 2</li>
          <li>Pinehurst No. 3</li>
          <li>Pinehurst No. 5</li>
          <li>The Cradle</li>
          <li>Southern Pines Golf Club</li>
          <li>Pine Needles Lodge & Golf Club</li>
          <li>Tobacco Road Golf Club</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Everything else on the site is clearly labeled as research-based — sourced from rankings, reviews, and conversations with golfers who've played them. I'll keep updating as I play more courses.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl text-dark-green font-bold mt-16">How this site is built</h2>
        <p>
          This is also a learning project. The site is built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a> and <a href="https://tailwindcss.com">Tailwind CSS</a>, hosted on Netlify, and the code is open source. Part of the goal is to learn modern web development, SEO, and content strategy by building something useful.
        </p>
        <p>
          There are no ads, no paywall, and no tracking beyond basic analytics. If affiliate links appear in the future, they'll be clearly disclosed and will never compromise the editorial honesty of the content.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl text-dark-green font-bold mt-16">Get in touch</h2>
        <p>
          Have a question about planning your trip? Spotted something inaccurate? Want to suggest a course or restaurant I should check out? <a href="/contact">Send me a message</a> — I'm happy to help.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
